uld%20exacerbate%20the%20supply%20problems%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20could%20suffer%20the%20consequences%20on%20the%20battlefield%2C%20according%20to%20Kathryn%20Levantovscaia%2C%20a%20deputy%20director%20in%20the%20Forward%20Defense%20program%20of%20the%20Atlantic%20Council's%20Scowcroft%20Center%20for%20Strategy%20and%20Security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRedirecting%20artillery%20to%20Israel%20would%20significantly%20hamper%20Ukraine's%20military%20operations%2C%20forcing%20them%20to%20scale%20back%20their%20efforts%20and%20ultimately%20increasing%20the%20risk%20to%20strategic%20positions%20and%20territory%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2240f8a5ad-f673-4da2-bb73-2c5e331f4708%5C%22%3ESignificant%20pressure%20on%20production%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20and%20Europe%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-forced-west-boost-weapon-production-gear-no-longer-made-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eramped%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%20artillery%20production%20rates%20to%20try%20to%20outgun%20Russia%20and%20meet%20Ukraine's%20battlefield%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEurope%20is%20making%20about%20600%2C000%20shells%20a%20year%2C%20per%20a%20December%202023%20Estonian%20Defense%20Ministry%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkaitseministeerium.ee%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fsetting_transatlantic_defence_up_for_success_0.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20the%20US%20produced%2028%2C000%20155mm%20rounds%20in%20March%2C%20with%20plans%20to%20produce%20up%20to%2080%2C000%20rounds%20a%20month%20by%20the%20end%20of%202024%2C%20Pentagon%20spokesperson%20Jeff%20Jurgensen%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.voanews.com%2Fa%2Fwithout-more-funds-us-unable-to-hit-ammunition-production-goals%2F7510881.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVOA%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Russia's%20production%20rates%20still%20far%20outweigh%20the%20West's%2C%20according%20to%20NATO%20intelligence%20estimates%20reported%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2024%2F03%2F10%2Fpolitics%2Frussia-artillery-shell-production-us-europe-ukraine%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECNN%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20March.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20despite%20the%20West's%20efforts%20to%20boost%20production%2C%20the%20US%20and%20European%20countries%20would%20struggle%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20artillery%20demand%20in%20two%20different%20wars%2C%20experts%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20one%20foresaw%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20lasting%20as%20long%20as%20it%20has%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20foresee%20Israel%20backing%20down%20any%20sooner%2C%20which%20means%20the%20simple%20cost%20of%20duration%20will%20inevitably%20impose%20a%20long-term%20strain%20on%20production%2C%26quot%3B%20Levantovscaia%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Temnycky%2C%20a%20nonresident%20fellow%20with%20the%20Atlantic%20Council's%20Eurasia%20Center%2C%20said%20the%20West's%20production%20capacities%20were%20already%20under%20pressure%20when%20Hamas%20launched%20its%20attack%20on%20Israel%20on%20October%207.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20a%20new%20war%20began%20on%20Israel's%20northern%20border%2C%20the%20West's%20industrial%20base%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bbrought%20to%20the%20test%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20with%20pressure%20to%20supply%20defense%20equipment%20to%20Israel%20and%20Ukraine%20at%20a%20faster%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20RAND's%20Cohen%2C%20%26quot%3Bany%20new%20demand%20would%20compound%20the%20supply%20issues%20with%20artillery%20rounds%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20he%20noted%20that%20Israel%20would%20fight%20a%20%26quot%3Bvery%26quot%3B%20different%20type%20of%20war%20with%20Hezbollah%20than%20Ukraine%20is%20fighting%20with%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIsrael%20would%20rely%20more%20on%20air%20power%2C%20and%20Hezbollah%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20would%20rely%20on%20its%20fairly%20significant%20stockpile%20of%20rockets%20and%20drones%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20so%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20you%20would%20see%20the%20same%20number%20of%20artillery%20duels%20that%20we%20see%20currently%20in%20Ukraine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Cancian%2C%20a%20retired%20Marine%20Corps%20colonel%20and%20senior%20advisor%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%2C%20has%20a%20different%20take.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESending%20thousands%20of%20rounds%20to%20Israel%20would%20reduce%20what%20is%20available%20for%20Ukraine%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bthat%20would%20be%20mitigated%20by%20the%20ongoing%20increase%20in%20production%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFurther%2C%20an%20Israeli%20conflict%20with%20Hezbollah%20would%20likely%20be%20of%20short%20duration%2C%20so%20shipments%20to%20Ukraine%20would%20return%20to%20previous%20levels%20when%20the%20war%20in%20Lebanon%20ended%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22695e6dc1-f761-4832-9117-b5e7e5c06e4a%5C%22%3EUkraine%20could%20pay%20a%20price%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECancian%20doesn't%20believe%20that%20Ukraine%20would%20run%20out%20of%20artillery%20projectiles.%20But%20it%20would%20need%20to%20prioritize%20targets%20as%20it%20did%20in%20the%20spring%2C%20when%20US%20supplies%20were%20drying%20up%2C%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20would%20lead%20to%20fewer%20Ukrainian%20counterattacks%20and%20a%20more%20difficult%20time%20holding%20terrain%20on%20the%20defensive%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELevantovscaia%20said%20diverting%20artillery%20to%20Israel%20could%20potentially%20cost%20Ukraine%20the%20war%2C%20but%20said%20she%20wasn't%20%26quot%3B100%25%20sold%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20Ukraine's%20innovation%20and%20determination%20could%20counterbalance%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECohen%20of%20RAND%2C%20for%20his%20part%2C%20said%20Ukraine%20has%20shown%20itself%20%26quot%3Bremarkably%20resilient%26quot%3B%20over%20the%20last%20two%20and%20a%20half%20years%20of%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMoreover%2C%20while%20the%20United%20States%20would%20want%20to%20support%20Israel%20in%20a%20war%20in%20the%20north%2C%20many%20European%20countries%20would%20likely%20still%20focus%20defense%20efforts%20on%20supporting%20Ukraine%20first%20and%20foremost%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bboth%20because%20they%20see%20Ukraine%20as%20vital%20to%20their%20national%20security%20and%20because%20sending%20arms%20to%20Israel%20is%20an%20even%20more%20contentious%20issue%20there%20than%20it%20is%20in%20the%20US.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20Temnycky%20said%20that%20any%20new%20limits%20on%20arms%20and%20ammunition%20would%20%26quot%3Bcertainly%26quot%3B%20make%20the%20objective%20of%20winning%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20harder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20%26quot%3BUkrainians%20have%20been%20fighting%20for%20true%20independence%20from%20Russia%20for%20over%20400%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20are%20determined%20to%20keep%20their%20freedom%2C%20and%20they%20will%20do%20whatever%20it%20takes%20to%20ensure%20that%20they%20do%20not%20lose%20the%20war.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-israel-war-could-strain-west-artillery-production-hurt-ukraine-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721819065000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F668ea0a6b2528216eeb511ca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-israel-war-could-strain-west-artillery-production-hurt-ukraine-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20war%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hezbollah%20could%20stretch%20the%20West's%20artillery%20production%2C%20and%20redirect%20artillery%20shells%20away%20from%20Ukraine%2C%20experts%20told%20BI.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tspirlet%40insider.com%20(Thibault%20Spirl